{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891495901,"sessionID":"ses_284a0a620ffehx8gAgnNxjHWNX","part":{"id":"prt_d7b61bbc6001yl8UwR36VbAK3u","messageID":"msg_d7b61b321001H74zmd5g3ZofSa","sessionID":"ses_284a0a620ffehx8gAgnNxjHWNX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6844b0bad7a44eeda43ea7116ca46254","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-036 Dify Plugin Integration\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-036\n5: - **Title**: Dify 插件集成\n6: - **Module**: integrations\n7: - **Language**: Python\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: Implementation deltas for adding Dify plugin integration to the AgentCube project, including the Python SDK client library and PCAP analyzer example application.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Create Dify plugin package structure\n18: \n19: The system SHALL create a complete Dify plugin package under `integrations/dify-plugin/` with all required manifest files, provider descriptors, tool definitions, and Python implementations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Plugin directory layout exists\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** a new `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n24: - **WHEN** the package structure is created\n25: - **THEN** the directory SHALL contain `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, and `.difyignore`\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ### Requirement: Implement plugin manifest\n30: \n31: The system SHALL implement `manifest.yaml` with all required fields including version, type, author, name, multilingual labels/descriptions, icons, resource permissions, tool provider references, and runner metadata.\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Manifest contains all required fields\n34: \n35: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml`\n36: - **WHEN** the file is parsed by Dify toolchain\n37: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version: 0.0.2`, `type: plugin`, `author: volcano-sh`, `name: agentcube`, `label` with multilingual map for `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR`, `description` with multilingual strings, `icon: icon.png`, `icon_dark: icon-dark.png`, `resource` subtree with `memory` and `permission` flags, `plugins.tools: [provider/agentcube.yaml]`, and `meta` with `version`, `arch` (amd64, arm64), `runner` (language: python, version: \"3.12\", entrypoint: main), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Implement provider descriptor\n42: \n43: The system SHALL implement `provider/agentcube.yaml` with identity fields and tool list pointing to the code interpreter tool.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Provider descriptor structure\n46: \n47: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml`\n48: - **WHEN** the provider is loaded by Dify\n49: - **THEN** the file SHALL contain `identity` with `author`, `name`, multilingual `label`, multilingual `description`, `icon`, a `tools` list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Implement tool schema\n54: \n55: The system SHALL implement `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` with the complete parameter schema for the code interpreter integration.\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Tool parameter schema\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n60: - **WHEN** the tool is configured in Dify\n61: - **THEN** the schema SHALL define `identity` with `name: agentcube-code-interpreter`, `author: agentcube`, multilingual `label` and `description`, and `parameters` array with `router_url` (string, required, form), `workload_manager_url` (string, required, form), `language` (select, options: python, javascript, typescript, llm), `code` (string, llm), `command` (string, llm), `session_id` (string, llm), `session_reuse` (boolean, llm), and `code_interpreter_id` (string, llm), each with `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, and `form` fields\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Requirement: Implement plugin main entry\n66: \n67: The system SHALL implement `main.py` that runs the Dify plugin framework with a 120-second request timeout.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Plugin process entrypoint\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n72: - **WHEN** Dify starts the plugin\n73: - **THEN** the file SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Implement provider class\n78: \n79: The system SHALL implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` class that extends `ToolProvider` with credential validation.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Provider class structure\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n84: - **WHEN** the provider class is instantiated\n85: - **THEN** it SHALL define `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider)` with `_validate_credentials` method that may raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError`\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: Implement tool class\n90: \n91: The system SHALL implement `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` class that extends `Tool` and delegates to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Tool class invocation\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n96: - **WHEN** Dify invokes the tool\n97: - **THEN** the class SHALL define `class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool)` with `_invoke` method that calls `execute(**tool_parameters)` and yields `create_json_message(result)`, and an `execute` method accepting `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language` (default \"python\"), `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse`, and delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: Create plugin dependencies\n102: \n103: The system SHALL create `requirements.txt` with pinned versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk`.\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Dependency specification\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n108: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n109: - **THEN** the file SHALL contain `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ### Requirement: Create Python SDK package\n114: \n115: The system SHALL create the complete `agentcube-sdk` Python package under `sdk-python/` with all client classes and utilities.\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: SDK package layout\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** `sdk-python/` directory\n120: - **WHEN** the SDK is structured\n121: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `pyproject.toml`, `agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`, `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `agentcube/exceptions.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`, `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`, `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`, `agentcube/utils/http.py`, `agentcube/utils/utils.py`, `agentcube/utils/log.py`, and `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Implement CodeInterpreterClient\n126: \n127: The system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterClient` with session management, file operations, code execution, and command execution.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Client initialization\n130: \n131: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n132: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated\n133: - **THEN** it SHALL accept `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url` (or from `ROUTER_URL` env), `auth_token`, `verbose`, and `session_id`, initialize `ControlPlaneClient` and `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and raise `ValueError` if `router_url` is not provided\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance used as context manager\n138: - **WHEN** the context exits\n139: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` which closes the data plane session, deletes the control plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Command execution with non-zero exit\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called\n144: - **WHEN** the remote command returns `exit_code != 0`\n145: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Python code execution\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language` as `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n150: - **WHEN** the code is executed\n151: - **THEN** the method SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: Implement AgentRuntimeClient\n156: \n157: The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` with session bootstrap, invocation, and lifecycle management.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Client initialization and session bootstrap\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n162: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated without `session_id`\n163: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`, raising `ValueError` if the header is missing\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeClient` instance with falsy `session_id`\n168: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: Implement ControlPlaneClient\n174: \n175: The system SHALL implement `ControlPlaneClient` with session creation and deletion via the Workload Manager API.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Create session\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` instance\n180: - **WHEN** `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` is called\n181: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body containing `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, and `metadata`, and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Delete session with 404\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** a `ControlPlaneClient` instance\n186: - **WHEN** `delete_session(session_id)` is called and server returns 404\n187: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### Requirement: Implement CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n192: \n193: The system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with file operations, command execution, and code execution via the Router API.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Execute command with timeout buffer\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instance\n198: - **WHEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=<value>)` posts to `api/execute`\n199: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON with `command` array and `timeout` string, and the read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: File write operation\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instance\n204: - **WHEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n205: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64-encoded `content`, `path`, and `mode: \"0644\"`\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Implement AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n210: \n211: The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with session bootstrap and invocation via the Router API.\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Invoke with timeout tuple\n214: \n215: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance\n216: - **WHEN** `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` is called\n217: - **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to 120\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ### Requirement: Implement exception hierarchy\n222: \n223: The system SHALL define the complete exception hierarchy in `agentcube/exceptions.py`.\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Exception classes defined\n226: \n227: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n228: - **WHEN** exceptions are imported\n229: - **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentCubeError` (base), `CommandExecutionError` (with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`), `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError`\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ### Requirement: Implement utility modules\n234: \n235: The system SHALL implement utility modules for HTTP session creation, token reading, and logging.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: HTTP session with pooling\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n240: - **WHEN** `create_session` is called\n241: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for both `http://` and `https://` with `pool_connections` and `pool_maxsize` defaulting to 10\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Token from file\n244: \n245: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n246: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(file_path)` is called\n247: - **THEN** it SHALL return file contents stripped, or empty string on `FileNotFoundError`\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ### Requirement: Configure SDK package metadata\n252: \n253: The system SHALL configure `pyproject.toml` with package metadata, dependencies, and build configuration.\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Package configuration\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `sdk-python/pyproject.toml`\n258: - **WHEN** the package is built\n259: - **THEN** it SHALL declare package name `agentcube-sdk`, `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`, dependencies including `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, and `cryptography`, build backend `setuptools.build_meta`, and package discovery for `agentcube*` modules\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer application\n264: \n265: The system SHALL create a FastAPI application under `example/pcap-analyzer/` that uses AgentCube code interpreters for PCAP analysis.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Application structure\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n270: - **WHEN** the example application is structured\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap_analyzer.py`, `requirements.txt`, `Dockerfile`, `deployment.yaml`, and `README.md`\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ### Requirement: Implement PCAP analyzer core classes\n276: \n277: The system SHALL implement `SandboxRunner`, agent builders, and analysis orchestration functions in `pcap_analyzer.py`.\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: SandboxRunner operations\n280: \n281: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` instance\n282: - **WHEN** methods are called\n283: - **THEN** it SHALL provide `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`, `upload_bytes(data, remote_path)`, `run(command)`, and `stop()` methods\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Agent builders\n286: \n287: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` imports\n288: - **WHEN** agent builders are called\n289: - **THEN** it SHALL provide `build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)`, `invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text)`, `build_planner_agent(llm)`, and `build_reporter_agent(llm)` functions\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: Analysis orchestration\n292: \n293: - **GIVEN** analysis functions\n294: - **WHEN** PCAP analysis is performed\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL provide `_plan_script`, `_repair_script`, `_execute_once_in_runner`, `_analyze_with_retries`, and `_report` functions\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ### Requirement: Implement PCAP analyzer endpoints\n300: \n301: The system SHALL implement FastAPI endpoints for startup validation and PCAP analysis.\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: Startup validation\n304: \n305: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` startup event\n306: - **WHEN** the application starts\n307: - **THEN** it SHALL fail if `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or configured API key) is not available, and build `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, and `REPORTER` agents\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint\n310: \n311: - **GIVEN** `POST /analyze` endpoint\n312: - **WHEN** called with either `pcap_file: UploadFile` or `pcap_path: str` form field\n313: - **THEN** it SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Configure PCAP analyzer environment\n318: \n319: The system SHALL configure environment variable bindings for OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Environment configuration\n322: \n323: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` configuration\n324: - **WHEN** the service starts\n325: - **THEN** it SHALL read `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_BASE` (default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`), `OPENAI_MODEL` (default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`), `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` (default `my-interpreter`), `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` (default `default`), and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` (default `5`)\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer dependencies\n330: \n331: The system SHALL create `requirements.txt` with all required Python dependencies.\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: Dependency list\n334: \n335: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n336: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed\n337: - **THEN** it SHALL include `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, and the full LangChain/LangGraph stack with pinned versions\n338: \n339: ---\n340: \n341: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer Dockerfile\n342: \n343: The system SHALL create a Dockerfile that builds the PCAP analyzer image with `uv` and vendors the agentcube SDK.\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Image build\n346: \n347: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile`\n348: - **WHEN** the image is built\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL use base `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`, run `uv venv`, install dependencies with `uv pip install`, copy `sdk-python/agentcube` to `./agentcube/`, copy `pcap_analyzer.py` to root, set `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, expose port 8000, and set `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n354: \n355: The system SHALL create `deployment.yaml` with Deployment manifest for the analyzer.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Deployment manifest\n358: \n359: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n360: - **WHEN** applied to cluster\n361: - **THEN** it SHALL create `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`, run container `pcap-analyzer` with image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, listen on TCP 8000, set resource requests `cpu: 200m` and `memory: 100Mi` with limits `cpu: 1` and `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets`, and set environment variables for all API and sandbox parameters\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ### Requirement: Create plugin documentation\n366: \n367: The system SHALL create `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, and `.difyignore` for the Dify plugin.\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Documentation files exist\n370: \n371: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n372: - **WHEN** documentation is complete\n373: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `GUIDE.md` with usage instructions, `README.md` with project overview, `PRIVACY.md` with privacy policy, and `.difyignore` with packaging exclusions\n374: \n375: ---\n376: \n377: ### Requirement: Create PCAP analyzer README\n378: \n379: The system SHALL create `README.md` for the PCAP analyzer example.\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Example documentation exists\n382: \n383: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n384: - **WHEN** documentation is complete\n385: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `README.md` with setup, usage, and deployment instructions\n386: \n387: ---\n388: \n389: ### Requirement: Ensure session header naming\n390: \n391: The system SHALL ensure all SDK Router requests use the lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: Session header consistency\n394: \n395: - **GIVEN** SDK data plane clients\n396: - **WHEN** making Router requests\n397: - **THEN** both `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL use header `x-agentcube-session-id` (with appropriate casing for the constant name)\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ### Requirement: Ensure timeout defaults\n402: \n403: The system SHALL ensure control-plane and data-plane clients default to 120-second read timeout and 5-second connect timeout.\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: Timeout defaults applied\n406: \n407: - **GIVEN** client initialization\n408: - **WHEN** no custom timeouts are provided\n409: - **THEN** `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL use `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0`\n410: \n411: ---\n412: \n413: ### Requirement: Handle router URL environment variable\n414: \n415: The system SHALL ensure `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` resolve `router_url` from argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable.\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: Router URL resolution\n418: \n419: - **GIVEN** client instantiation\n420: - **WHEN** `router_url` is not provided as argument\n421: - **THEN** both clients SHALL read from `ROUTER_URL` environment variable and raise `ValueError` if not set\n422: \n423: ---\n424: \n425: ### Requirement: Handle workload manager URL and auth token\n426: \n427: The system SHALL ensure `ControlPlaneClient` resolves `workload_manager_url` from argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env, and `auth_token` from argument or SA token file.\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: Workload Manager configuration\n430: \n431: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` instantiation\n432: - **WHEN** `workload_manager_url` is not provided\n433: - **THEN** it SHALL read from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n434: \n435: #### Scenario: Auth token resolution\n436: \n437: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` instantiation without `auth_token`\n438: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n439: - **THEN** it SHALL read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file` and set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header if token is non-empty\n440: \n441: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n442: \n443: 1. ✅ Dify plugin package structure created with all required files\n444: 2. ✅ Plugin manifest includes all required fields\n445: 3. ✅ Provider descriptor properly configured\n446: 4. ✅ Tool schema with complete parameter definitions\n447: 5. ✅ Plugin main entry point runs Dify framework\n448: 6. ✅ Provider class with credential validation\n449: 7. ✅ Tool class delegates to agentcube SDK\n450: 8. ✅ Plugin dependencies pinned correctly\n451: 9. ✅ Python SDK package structure complete\n452: 10. ✅ CodeInterpreterClient implements session management\n453: 11. ✅ AgentRuntimeClient implements session bootstrap and invocation\n454: 12. ✅ ControlPlaneClient implements session CRUD operations\n455: 13. ✅ CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient implements file and command operations\n456: 14. ✅ AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient implements invocation with session management\n457: 15. ✅ Exception hierarchy defined\n458: 16. ✅ Utility modules for HTTP, token, and logging\n459: 17. ✅ SDK package metadata configured\n460: 18. ✅ PCAP analyzer application structure\n461: 19. ✅ PCAP analyzer core classes and orchestration\n462: 20. ✅ PCAP analyzer FastAPI endpoints\n463: 21. ✅ PCAP analyzer environment configuration\n464: 22. ✅ PCAP analyzer dependencies specified\n465: 23. ✅ PCAP analyzer Dockerfile\n466: 24. ✅ PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n467: 25. ✅ Plugin documentation files\n468: 26. ✅ PCAP analyzer documentation\n469: 27. ✅ Session header naming consistent\n470: 28. ✅ Timeout defaults applied\n471: 29. ✅ Router URL environment variable handling\n472: 30. ✅ Workload manager URL and auth token handling\n473: \n474: ## Dependencies\n475: \n476: - `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n477: - `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n478: - `requests`\n479: - `PyJWT>=2.0.0`\n480: - `cryptography`\n481: - `fastapi==0.120.0`\n482: - `uvicorn==0.38.0`\n483: - LangChain/LangGraph stack\n484: - Python >=3.10\n485: \n486: ## References\n487: \n488: - Base Design: `integrations/design.md`\n489: - Base Specification: `integrations/spec.md`\n490: - Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n491: - Base Specification: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n492: - AR: AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n\n(End of file - total 492 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-036 Dify Plugin Integration\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-036\n- **Title**: Dify 插件集成\n- **Module**: integrations\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplementation deltas for adding Dify plugin integration to the AgentCube project, including the Python SDK client library and PCAP analyzer example application.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Create Dify plugin package structure\n\nThe system SHALL create a complete Dify plugin package under `integrations/dify-plugin/` with all required manifest files, provider descriptors, tool definitions, and Python implementations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775891495883,"end":1775891495897}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775891495927,"sessionID":"ses_284a0a620ffehx8gAgnNxjHWNX","part":{"id":"prt_d7b61bbdc0013Gvt9uyTLPK5hJ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b61b321001H74zmd5g3ZofSa","sessionID":"ses_284a0a620ffehx8gAgnNxjHWNX","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":42956,"input":208,"output":61,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":42687}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775891498998,"sessionID":"ses_284a0a620ffehx8gAgnNxjHWNX","part":{"id":"prt_d7b61c7f4001XuLFqtdcpCftI4","messageID":"msg_d7b61bc11001lPemgVN6Rj6CFw","sessionID":"ses_284a0a620ffehx8gAgnNxjHWNX","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891605833,"sessionID":"ses_284a0a620ffehx8gAgnNxjHWNX","part":{"id":"prt_d7b636872001GZ5a5suluN0zmf","messageID":"msg_d7b61bc11001lPemgVN6Rj6CFw","sessionID":"ses_284a0a620ffehx8gAgnNxjHWNX","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-89373524b59f438d80949d43e2f9520b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# delta-spec: AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n\n## Overview\n\nModule: `pkg/workloadmanager`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: L\nTask: Add comprehensive unit tests for untested components\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Unit tests for auth/k8s_auth.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for K8sAuthenticator and TokenCache components.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-001: K8sAuthenticator authenticates valid token\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface and audience\nAND a valid Kubernetes service account token\nWHEN Authenticate is called with the token\nTHEN the AuthenticationInfo should be returned containing username, UID, and groups\nAND no error should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-002: K8sAuthenticator rejects invalid token\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface and audience\nAND an invalid/expired Kubernetes token\nWHEN Authenticate is called with the invalid token\nTHEN an error should be returned\nAND the error message should indicate authentication failed\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-003: K8sAuthenticator handles TokenReview API failure\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface\nAND the TokenReview API returns an error\nWHEN Authenticate is called\nTHEN an error should be returned\nAND the error should wrap the underlying API error\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-004: TokenCache stores and retrieves valid entry\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 5 minutes\nAND an AuthenticationInfo object\nWHEN Put is called with a token and the info\nAND Get is called with the same token before TTL expires\nTHEN the AuthenticationInfo should be returned\nAND the second return value should be true\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-005: TokenCache returns false for non-existent token\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 5 minutes\nWHEN Get is called with a token that was never stored\nTHEN nil should be returned\nAND the second return value should be false\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-006: TokenCache expires entries after TTL\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 1 millisecond\nAND an AuthenticationInfo object stored with Put\nWHEN the cache is waited for 2 milliseconds\nAND Get is called with the token\nTHEN nil should be returned\nAND the second return value should be false\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-007: TokenCache Delete removes entry\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a TokenCache with a stored token entry\nWHEN Delete is called with the token\nAND Get is called with the same token\nTHEN nil should be returned\nAND the second return value should be false\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-008: TokenCache Cleanup removes expired entries\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 1 millisecond\nAND multiple token entries stored\nWHEN the cache is waited for 2 milliseconds\nAND Cleanup is called\nTHEN expired entries should be removed from the cache\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-009: TokenCache is thread-safe for concurrent reads\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a TokenCache with multiple stored entries\nAND multiple goroutines calling Get concurrently\nTHEN no race condition should occur\nAND all reads should return consistent results\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-010: TokenCache is thread-safe for concurrent writes\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a TokenCache\nAND multiple goroutines calling Put with different tokens concurrently\nTHEN no race condition should occur\nAND all entries should be stored correctly\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/predicates.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for event predicates and helper functions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-011: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns true on generation change\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld generation = 1\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew generation = 2\nWHEN Update is called with the event\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-012: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns false on same generation\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld generation = 1\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew generation = 1\nWHEN Update is called with the event\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-013: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns false on nil objects\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld = nil\nOR ObjectNew = nil\nWHEN Update is called with the event\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-014: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label added\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"value\", \"newKey\": \"newValue\"}\nWHEN Update is called with the event\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-015: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label modified\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"oldValue\"}\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"newValue\"}\nWHEN Update is called with the event\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-016: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label removed\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key1\": \"value1\", \"key2\": \"value2\"}\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key1\": \"value1\"}\nWHEN Update is called with the event\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-017: LabelChangedPredicate returns false on unchanged labels\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\nWHEN Update is called with the event\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-018: AnnotationChangedPredicate returns true on annotation change\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an AnnotationChangedPredicate\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld annotations = {\"key\": \"value\"}\nAND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew annotations = {\"key\": \"newValue\"}\nWHEN Update is called with the event\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-019: PauseAnnotationPredicate returns true when not paused\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a PauseAnnotationPredicate\nAND a CreateEvent with Object annotations = {}\nWHEN Create is called with the event\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-020: PauseAnnotationPredicate returns false when paused\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a PauseAnnotationPredicate\nAND a CreateEvent with Object annotations = {\"agentcube.volcano.sh/paused\": \"true\"}\nWHEN Create is called with the event\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-021: IsBeingDeleted returns true for object with deletion timestamp\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with DeletionTimestamp set\nWHEN IsBeingDeleted is called with the object\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-022: IsBeingDeleted returns false for object without deletion timestamp\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with zero DeletionTimestamp\nWHEN IsBeingDeleted is called with the object\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-023: HasOwnerReference returns true when owner reference exists\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with OwnerReferences containing an owner with UID \"test-uid\"\nWHEN HasOwnerReference is called with the object and UID \"test-uid\"\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-024: HasOwnerReference returns false when owner reference missing\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with OwnerReferences not containing UID \"missing-uid\"\nWHEN HasOwnerReference is called with the object and UID \"missing-uid\"\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-025: AddOwnerReference adds owner reference to object\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a child client.Object\nAND an owner client.Object\nWHEN AddOwnerReference is called with child and owner\nTHEN the child should have the owner in its OwnerReferences\nAND the owner reference should have the correct APIVersion, Kind, UID, and Name\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-026: AddLabels adds labels to object\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with labels = {\"existing\": \"value\"}\nWHEN AddLabels is called with labels = {\"new\": \"label\"}\nTHEN the object should have labels = {\"existing\": \"value\", \"new\": \"label\"}\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-027: AddLabels initializes empty labels map\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with nil labels\nWHEN AddLabels is called with labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\nTHEN the object should have labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-028: AddAnnotations adds annotations to object\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with annotations = {\"existing\": \"value\"}\nWHEN AddAnnotations is called with annotations = {\"new\": \"annotation\"}\nTHEN the object should have annotations = {\"existing\": \"value\", \"new\": \"annotation\"}\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-029: IsPodReady returns true for ready pod\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a Pod with PodReady condition status = ConditionTrue\nWHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-030: IsPodReady returns false for not ready pod\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a Pod with PodReady condition status = ConditionFalse\nWHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-031: IsPodReady returns false for pod without ready condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a Pod without PodReady condition\nWHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-032: GetPodCondition returns matching condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a Pod with conditions including PodReady\nWHEN GetPodCondition is called with PodReady type\nTHEN the PodReady condition should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-033: GetPodCondition returns nil for missing condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a Pod without Ready condition\nWHEN GetPodCondition is called with Ready type\nTHEN nil should be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/finalizers.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for finalizer management functions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-034: AddFinalizer adds finalizer to object\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a context\nAND a mock client.Client\nAND a client.Object without finalizers\nWHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\nTHEN the object should have \"test-finalizer\" in its finalizers list\nAND no error should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-035: AddFinalizer does not add duplicate finalizer\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a context\nAND a mock client.Client\nAND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"existing\", \"test-finalizer\"]\nWHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\nTHEN the object should still have only two finalizers\nAND no error should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-036: AddFinalizer handles patch error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a context\nAND a mock client.Client that returns an error on Patch\nAND a client.Object without finalizers\nWHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\nTHEN an error should be returned\nAND the error message should contain \"failed to add finalizer\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-037: RemoveFinalizer removes finalizer from object\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a context\nAND a mock client.Client\nAND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"keep-me\", \"remove-me\"]\nWHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"remove-me\"\nTHEN the object should have only [\"keep-me\"] in its finalizers\nAND no error should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-038: RemoveFinalizer does nothing when finalizer not present\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a context\nAND a mock client.Client\nAND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"keep-me\"]\nWHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"not-present\"\nTHEN the object should still have [\"keep-me\"] in its finalizers\nAND no error should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-039: RemoveFinalizer handles patch error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a context\nAND a mock client.Client that returns an error on Patch\nAND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"test-finalizer\"]\nWHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\nTHEN an error should be returned\nAND the error message should contain \"failed to remove finalizer\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-040: HasFinalizer returns true when finalizer present\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with finalizers = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]\nWHEN HasFinalizer is called with \"b\"\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-041: HasFinalizer returns false when finalizer absent\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a client.Object with finalizers = [\"a\", \"c\"]\nWHEN HasFinalizer is called with \"b\"\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-042: GetOwnerReference returns UID when matching owner found\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a metav1.Object with OwnerReferences\nAND one reference has APIVersion = \"v1\", Kind = \"Pod\", and UID = \"test-uid\"\nWHEN GetOwnerReference is called with APIVersion = \"v1\" and Kind = \"Pod\"\nTHEN \"test-uid\" and true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-043: GetOwnerReference returns empty when no matching owner\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a metav1.Object with OwnerReferences\nAND none have the specified APIVersion and Kind\nWHEN GetOwnerReference is called with non-matching APIVersion and Kind\nTHEN empty string and false should be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/status.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for status condition management functions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-044: SetCondition adds new condition to empty list\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a nil conditions pointer\nAND a conditionType, status, reason, and message\nWHEN SetCondition is called\nTHEN a new condition should be added to the list\nAND the condition should have the specified type, status, reason, and message\nAND LastTransitionTime should be set to current time\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-045: SetCondition updates existing condition with new status\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with a Ready condition with status = False\nAND new status = True\nWHEN SetCondition is called with Ready type and new status\nTHEN the Ready condition should be updated to status = True\nAND LastTransitionTime should be updated to current time\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-046: SetCondition updates existing condition with same status\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with a Ready condition with status = True\nAND new status = True\nWHEN SetCondition is called with Ready type and same status\nTHEN the Ready condition should retain status = True\nAND LastTransitionTime should be updated to current time\nAND reason and message should be updated\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-047: GetCondition returns matching condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Ready, Available, and Progressing conditions\nWHEN GetCondition is called with Ready type\nTHEN the Ready condition should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-048: GetCondition returns nil for missing condition type\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\nWHEN GetCondition is called with Error type\nTHEN nil should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-049: IsReady returns true when Ready condition is true\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition status = ConditionTrue\nWHEN IsReady is called\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-050: IsReady returns false when Ready condition is false\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition status = ConditionFalse\nWHEN IsReady is called\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-051: IsReady returns false when Ready condition missing\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list without Ready condition\nWHEN IsReady is called\nTHEN false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-052: IsAvailable returns true when Available condition is true\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Available condition status = ConditionTrue\nWHEN IsAvailable is called\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-053: IsProgressing returns true when Progressing condition is true\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Progressing condition status = ConditionTrue\nWHEN IsProgressing is called\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-054: HasError returns true when Error condition is true\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Error condition status = ConditionTrue\nWHEN HasError is called\nTHEN true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-055: SetReadyCondition sets Ready condition to true\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a nil conditions pointer\nWHEN SetReadyCondition is called with ready = true\nTHEN a Ready condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-056: SetReadyCondition sets Ready condition to false\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions pointer with Ready condition\nWHEN SetReadyCondition is called with ready = false\nTHEN the Ready condition should have status = ConditionFalse\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-057: SetErrorCondition sets Error condition with error message\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a nil conditions pointer\nAND an error with message \"test error\"\nWHEN SetErrorCondition is called with the error\nTHEN an Error condition should be added\nAND the message should contain \"test error\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-058: SetErrorCondition sets Error condition without error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions pointer\nAND nil error\nWHEN SetErrorCondition is called with nil error\nTHEN an Error condition with empty message should be set\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-059: ClearErrorCondition removes Error condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Error condition\nWHEN ClearErrorCondition is called\nTHEN the Error condition should be removed from the list\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-060: ClearErrorCondition does nothing when Error condition missing\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\nWHEN ClearErrorCondition is called\nTHEN the conditions list should remain unchanged\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-061: SetProgressingCondition sets Progressing condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a nil conditions pointer\nWHEN SetProgressingCondition is called with progressing = true\nTHEN a Progressing condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-062: SetAvailableCondition sets Available condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a nil conditions pointer\nWHEN SetAvailableCondition is called with available = true\nTHEN an Available condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-063: SetSandboxCreatedCondition sets SandboxCreated condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a nil conditions pointer\nWHEN SetSandboxCreatedCondition is called with created = true\nTHEN a SandboxCreated condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-064: GetConditionMessage returns condition message\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition message = \"ready message\"\nWHEN GetConditionMessage is called with Ready type\nTHEN \"ready message\" should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-065: GetConditionMessage returns empty string for missing condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\nWHEN GetConditionMessage is called with Error type\nTHEN empty string should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-066: GetConditionReason returns condition reason\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition reason = \"ReadyReason\"\nWHEN GetConditionReason is called with Ready type\nTHEN \"ReadyReason\" should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-067: GetConditionReason returns empty string for missing condition\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\nWHEN GetConditionReason is called with Error type\nTHEN empty string should be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/errors.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for ReconcilerError types and constructors.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-068: ReconcilerError.Error returns formatted message with wrapped error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"TestCode\", Message = \"Test message\", and Err = errors.New(\"wrapped\")\nWHEN Error is called\nTHEN the result should contain \"TestCode: Test message (caused by: wrapped)\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-069: ReconcilerError.Error returns formatted message without wrapped error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"TestCode\", Message = \"Test message\", and Err = nil\nWHEN Error is called\nTHEN the result should be \"TestCode: Test message\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-070: ReconcilerError.Unwrap returns wrapped error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ReconcilerError with Err = errors.New(\"wrapped\")\nWHEN Unwrap is called\nTHEN the wrapped error should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-071: ReconcilerError.Unwrap returns nil when no wrapped error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a ReconcilerError with Err = nil\nWHEN Unwrap is called\nTHEN nil should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-072: NewReconcilerError creates error with all fields\n```gherkin\nGIVEN code, message, err, and retryable parameters\nWHEN NewReconcilerError is called\nTHEN a ReconcilerError with all fields set should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-073: NewValidationFailedError creates non-retryable error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN message and err parameters\nWHEN NewValidationFailedError is called\nTHEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"ValidationFailed\" and Retryable = false should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-074: NewSandboxCreateFailedError creates retryable error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN message and err parameters\nWHEN NewSandboxCreateFailedError is called\nTHEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxCreateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-075: NewSandboxUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN message and err parameters\nWHEN NewSandboxUpdateFailedError is called\nTHEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-076: NewSandboxDeleteFailedError creates retryable error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN message and err parameters\nWHEN NewSandboxDeleteFailedError is called\nTHEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-077: NewStatusUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN message and err parameters\nWHEN NewStatusUpdateFailedError is called\nTHEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"StatusUpdateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-078: NewFinalizerFailedError creates retryable error\n```gherkin\nGIVEN message and err parameters\nWHEN NewFinalizerFailedError is called\nTHEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"FinalizerFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/controller.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for controller setup and configuration functions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-079: DefaultControllerConfig returns sensible defaults\n```gherkin\nGIVEN no configuration provided\nWHEN DefaultControllerConfig is called\nTHEN RequeueAfter should be 10 seconds\nAND MaxConcurrentReconciles should be 2\nAND EnableLeaderElection should be true\nAND LeaderElectionID should be \"agentcube-reconciler\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-080: NewControllerManager creates manager with config\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a rest.Config\nAND a ControllerConfig with custom values\nWHEN NewControllerManager is called\nTHEN a ctrl.Manager should be returned\nAND the manager should use the specified scheme\nAND no error should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-081: NewControllerManager handles error from ctrl.NewManager\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an invalid rest.Config\nAND a ControllerConfig\nWHEN NewControllerManager is called\nTHEN an error should be returned\nAND the error message should contain \"unable to start manager\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-082: GetSandboxName returns formatted name\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a workload name \"test-workload\"\nWHEN GetSandboxName is called\nTHEN \"test-workload-sandbox\" should be returned\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-083: GetSandboxName handles empty workload name\n```gherkin\nGIVEN an empty workload name\nWHEN GetSandboxName is called\nTHEN \"-sandbox\" should be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/metrics.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for Prometheus metrics recording functions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-084: RecordReconciliation increments reconcileTotal counter\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordReconciliation is called with controller, namespace, name, duration, and result\nTHEN reconcileTotal counter should be incremented\nAND reconcileDuration histogram should observe the duration\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-085: RecordReconciliation increments reconcileRequeues on error result\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordReconciliation is called with result = \"error\"\nTHEN reconcileRequeues counter should be incremented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-086: RecordReconciliationError increments reconcileErrors counter\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordReconciliationError is called\nTHEN reconcileErrors counter should be incremented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-087: RecordRequeue increments reconcileRequeues counter\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordRequeue is called\nTHEN reconcileRequeues counter should be incremented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-088: RecordResourceReady increments resourcesReady gauge\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordResourceReady is called\nTHEN resourcesReady gauge should be incremented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-089: RecordResourcePending increments resourcesPending gauge\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordResourcePending is called\nTHEN resourcesPending gauge should be incremented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-090: RecordResourceError increments resourcesError gauge\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordResourceError is called\nTHEN resourcesError gauge should be incremented\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-091: ClearResourceMetrics resets resource gauges to zero\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics with non-zero values\nWHEN ClearResourceMetrics is called\nTHEN resourcesReady gauge should be set to 0\nAND resourcesPending gauge should be set to 0\nAND resourcesError gauge should be set to 0\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-092: RecordSandboxCreation increments sandboxCreations counter\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordSandboxCreation is called\nTHEN sandboxCreations counter should be incremented\nAND sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-093: RecordSandboxDeletion increments sandboxDeletions counter\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordSandboxDeletion is called\nTHEN sandboxDeletions counter should be incremented\nAND sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-094: RecordSandboxUpdate records update duration\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\nWHEN RecordSandboxUpdate is called\nTHEN sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration with operation = \"update\"\n```\n\n#### SCENARIO-095: ResetMetrics resets all metrics\n```gherkin\nGIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics with non-zero values\nWHEN ResetMetrics is called\nTHEN all metric counters should be reset\nAND all metric histograms should be reset\nAND all metric gauges should be reset\n```\n\n---\n\n## Non-Requirements (Excluded from this task)\n\nThe following files are excluded as they contain only constants, plain structs, or are better tested with integration tests:\n\n- `defaults.go` - Contains only constants\n- `api/types.go` - Contains only plain struct definitions\n- `types/sandbox_types.go` - Contains only plain struct definitions\n- `server/server.go` - Server lifecycle is better tested with integration/end-to-end tests\n- `controller/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go` - Complex reconciler logic is better tested with integration tests using envtest\n\n---\n\n## Test Coverage Goals\n\nTarget coverage: **≥ 80%** for all tested files\n\nPriority order:\n1. `auth/k8s_auth.go` - Critical security component\n2. `controller/reconciler/predicates.go` - Core event filtering logic\n3. `controller/reconciler/finalizers.go` - Resource cleanup safety\n4. `controller/reconciler/status.go` - State management\n5. `controller/reconciler/errors.go` - Error handling\n6. `controller/reconciler/controller.go` - Controller setup\n7. `controller/reconciler/metrics.go` - Observability\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `k8s.io/client-go` - Kubernetes client library (for mocks in auth tests)\n- `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` - Controller runtime (for mock client in reconciler tests)\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` - Prometheus client (for metrics tests)\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify` - Testing assertions and mocks\n- `github.com/golang/mock` - Mock generation for k8s interfaces","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/gc/collector.go\">\nERROR [200:36] c.storeClient.GetSandbox undefined (type store.Store has no field or method GetSandbox)\nERROR [221:30] a.store.GetSandbox undefined (type store.Store has no field or method GetSandbox)\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<dia